ping the highlighted cells makes all the rows palindromic.\n\nExample 2:\n\nInput: grid = [[0,1],[0,1],[0,0]]\nOutput: 1\nExplanation:\n\nFlipping the highlighted cell makes all the columns palindromic.\n\nExample 3:\n\nInput: grid = [[1],[0]]\nOutput: 0\nExplanation:\nAll rows are already palindromic.\n\n \nConstraints:\n\nm == grid.length\nn == grid[i].length\n1 <= m * n <= 2 * 105\n0 <= grid[i][j] <= 1\n\n\n\n### Format: You will use the following starter code to write the solution to the problem and enclose your code within delimiters.\n```python\nclass Solution:\n    def minFlips(self, grid: List[List[int]]) -> int:\n        \n```\n\n### Answer: (use the provided format with backticks)\n", "response": "```python\nfrom typing import List\n\nclass Solution:\n    def minFlips(self, grid: List[List[int]]) -> int:\n        m, n = len(grid), len(grid[0])\n        \n        def flips_to_palindrome(row_or_col):\n            flips = 0\n            for i in range(len(row_or_col) // 2):\n                if row_or_col[i] != row_or_col[-i-1]:\n                    flips += 1\n            return flips\n        \n        # Calculate the number of flips needed to make each row palindromic\n        row_flips = [flips_to_palindrome(grid[i]) for i in range(m)]\n        # Calculate the number of flips needed to make each column palindromic\n        col_flips = [flips_to_palindrome([grid[j][i] for j in range(m)]) for i in range(n)]\n        \n        # Total flips to make all rows palindromic\n        min_row_flips = sum(row_flips)\n        # Total flips to make all columns palindromic\n        min_col_flips = sum(col_flips)\n        \n        # Choose the minimum of the two\n        return min(min_row_flips, min_col_flips)\n```\n\nThis solution calculates the minimum number of flips needed to make either all rows or all columns palindromic in the given binary matrix. It does this by first defining a helper function `flips_to_palindrome` to calculate the number of flips needed to make a single row or column palindromic. It then computes the total flips needed for all rows and all columns and returns the minimum of these two values.", "estimated_date": 1722124800000}